{{Citation needed|date=October 4, 2015}} '''Samaya Symbols''' (三昧耶形, さんまやぎょう/さまやぎょう) are symbolic objects used in {{ill|Esoteric Buddhism|ja|密教|12=draft|12=draft}} to represent specific {{ill|Buddhas|ja|仏|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Bodhisattvas|ja|菩薩|12=draft|12=draft}}. They are also referred to as '''Sanmyō''' (三形) in abbreviated form.
The term ''samaya'' originates from the {{ill|Sanskrit|ja|サンスクリット語|12=draft|12=draft}} word for "promise" or "contract," indicating a prearranged agreement, as established in Buddhist scriptures, on which symbols represent specific Buddhas.
Traditionally, these symbols are defined as the manifestation of a Buddha’s vow or aspiration to save all sentient beings. Each symbol is inherently connected to the respective Buddha's spiritual essence.
== Characteristics == In most cases, the samaya symbol corresponds directly to the Buddha's or Bodhisattva's {{ill|attributes|ja|持物|12=draft|12=draft}}. For example: * For {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|12=draft|12=draft}}, the sword ({{ill|Kurikara sword|ja|倶利伽羅剣|12=draft|12=draft}}) serves as the samaya symbol. * For {{ill|Shō Kannon|ja|聖観音|12=draft|12=draft}}, a lotus blossom is used. * For {{ill|Kokūzō Bosatsu|ja|虚空蔵菩薩|12=draft|12=draft}}, the wish-fulfilling jewel ({{ill|Cintāmaṇi|ja|如意宝珠|12=draft|12=draft}}) represents the samaya symbol.
In some instances, when a Buddha traditionally lacks attributes, such as in the case of the {{ill|Tathagata|ja|如来|12=draft|12=draft}}, special objects are designated as their samaya symbols. For instance: * {{ill|Dainichi Nyorai|ja|大日如来|12=draft|12=draft}} is often represented by a {{ill|treasure stupa|ja|宝塔|1=Treasure Pagoda|2=de|3=Schatzpagode|4=ja|5=宝塔|1=Treasure Pagoda|12=draft|12=draft}}. * Alternatively, certain hand gestures ({{ill|Mudras|ja|印相|12=draft|12=draft}}) may serve as samaya symbols.
== Usage in Mandalas == Samaya symbols are frequently depicted in Buddhist art, including {{ill|mandalas|ja|曼荼羅|12=draft|12=draft}}. Instead of depicting full-bodied Buddhas or Bodhisattvas, their respective symbols are used to represent them. Notable examples include: * The {{ill|Vajradhatu Mandala|ja|金剛界曼荼羅|12=draft|12=draft}} within its Samaya Assembly (三昧耶会). * The ''Samaya Assembly of Trailokyavijaya'' ({{ill|降三世三昧耶会|ja|降三世三昧耶会|12=draft|12=draft}}).
== References == {{Citation needed|section}} {{Reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|Attributes in art|ja|アトリビュート|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Buddhist symbolism|en|Buddhist symbolism|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Mudras|ja|印相|12=draft|12=draft}} * [[:en:Seed_syllable|seed syllable]] {{Buddhism}}
